From: Catriona Scheffer <Catriona.Scheffer@ansys.com>
Sent: Thursday, February 11, 2021 9:42 PM
To: Abdul Lateef Khan <abdullateef.khan@ku.ac.ae>
Subject: RE: Lumerical license renewal

 

Hello Abdul,

 

I outlined most of the differences in my previous email.  The packages are very similar.

Previously you purchased our Silver Site License which came with 30 FDTD licenses and 20 licenses of our other products, MODE, DGTD, HEAT, FEEM, CHARGE, MQW, STACK and INTERCONNECT.  You also purchase our  virtuoso interop license. The cost was 25,920 USD excluding duties and taxes.

 

This year we have a 25 Task Research bundle which includes 25 licenses of each of our products as well as all our interoperability products and cml compiler. Each GUI license comes with 4 engines with a 32  core limit each.  Our products, including our intereroperability products may be found on our website,  https://www.lumerical.com/products/  The 1 year cost is 24,800.00 USD excluding duties and taxes.

 

The cost is lower this year than previously.  The main differences are you only have 25 FDTD rather than 30.  However, you also have all of our interoperability licenses and the cml compiler, previously not  included.

 

Best regards,

Catriona

 

 

 


